headline.0: Another Day, Another Death: A Mother Dies in Prison After Reporting Threats
headline.1: Why South Dakota's Senate Race is Not Like Kansas

short_description.0: Latandra Ellington, a 36-year old mother of four children, died in a Florida prison last week.  Ellington had just seven months left to serve of her twenty-two month sentence for grand theft when she was found dead in her cell.
short_description.1: Dramatic developments last week in the South Dakota Senate race have left national political observers scrambling to make sense of it.
